Oxford
Oxford
Oxfordshire wildlife park hand-rears first armadillo pups
3 May 2016
From the section Oxford
Image copyright
Paul Nicholls
Image caption
The "strong and healthy" armadillo pups were rejected by their mother
A keeper at Cotswold Wildlife Park is hand-rearing its first new-born armadillos after they were rejected by their mother.Twins Amelia and Wallace have been staying in primate keeper Stacey Axeman's flat, where she has been acting as their surrogate mum.Now they have moved to the Oxfordshire park, but are not yet on display.The "strong and healthy" pair could join another collection as part of the European Breeding Programme (EEP).Their parents Linda and Lucas are currently on show at the park near Burford.
Image copyright
Paul Nicholls
Image caption
The armadillos are the first to have been successfully bred at the park
Image copyright
Paul Nicholls
Image caption
Primate keeper Stacey Axeman has been hand-rearing the twins
